------------- Static variable ------------------
Static variable :
Static variables in Java belong to the class rather than individual objects,
meaning they share a single memory location across all instances and retain their value throughout the program's lifecycle.

Key Characteristics :
Static variables get initialized when the class loads,
They can be accessed via the class name (preferred)
Declaration Syntax : Use the static keyword before the data type and variable name: static data_type variable_name;

------------- Final ------------------
Final Variable :
In Java, a final variable is a variable whose value can be assigned only once and cannot be changed (reassigned) afterwards.

public static void main(String[] args) {
        final int MAX_VALUE = 100;   // initialize once
        System.out.println("MAX_VALUE = " + MAX_VALUE);

        // MAX_VALUE = 200;          // ❌ compile-time error: cannot assign a value to final variable
    }


